CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Flash Newspicture Magazine, February 14, 1938, pg. 23, reads: "'Woogie' Harris the famous Pgh. sportsman authoritatively informs the beautiful Lena of the air lanes to the film colony as the future 'sepian Eleanor Powell' effuses one of her captivating smiles."Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 5, 1938, pg. 13, reads: "Lena Horne is shown here with William A. Harris, Pittsburgh sportsman, checking up T. W. A. flight tables, preparatory to board a plane to Hollywood, where she will be co-starred in a movie..."
TitMainTitle: Lena Horne and William "Woogie" Harris with TWA ticket folders in front of airline schedule at Allegheny County Municipal Airport
